"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42037","Speaker's Committee on the Electorial Commission","false","2014-04-01","<p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission informs me that the confirmation dry run involved matching all entries on the electoral registers against the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) Customer Information System database. Entries would be marked as green if they matched with DWP, amber if they were a partial match or red if there was no match.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Results for all wards are available on the Commission's website here: <a href="http://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/excel_doc/0003/163146/Confirmation-dry-run-2013-Results-Wards.xls" target="_blank">http://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/excel_doc/0003/163146/Confirmation-dry-run-2013-Results-Wards.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The ward results for Sandwell Council, Walsall Council, Wolverhampton City Council and Birmingham City Council will be deposited in the Library.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42037/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42037/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42037/answer","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42037/answer/previousversion/2093","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","36",,,"2014-03-07",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, what the electoral registration figures were in each ward in the recent confirmation dry run conducted in (a) Sandwell Metropolitan Borough, (b) Walsall Metropolitan Borough, (c) Wolverhampton Metropolitan Borough and (d) Birmingham City.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","191130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42044","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-17","<p> </p><p> </p><p>DWP does make claimants aware of relevant support services, but will always consider whether it has provision first.</p><p>Short Term Benefit Advance awards are available to those entitled to them prior to initial payment of benefit, almost 100% of applications are routinely processed within 24 hours.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-03-17T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42044/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42044/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42044/answer",,,,,"29",,,"2014-03-07",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will assess the potential for improved administration and awareness of the short-term benefit advances scheme to affect demand for food banks; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","191156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42045","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-17","<p /> <p /> <p>DWP has a quality framework in place for checking the accuracy of Short Term Benefit Advance decisions. In February 2014, checks confirmed 96% accuracy of application decisions. In terms of timeliness, an average 98% of all application decisions made throughout the operational year since April 2013 were made within 24 hours.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-03-17T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42045/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42045/answer",,,,,"29",,,"2014-03-07",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the quality of the administration of the short-term benefit advances scheme since its inception.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","191105"
