ay 2010. This should be seen in relation to the 871,802 prisoners handled by the escort service in 2012-13 alone.</p><p> </p><p>Table 4 shows the number of escapes in transit, in each month between May 2010 and March 2013. All these prisoners have subsequently been recaptured.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table 4 Month and category of prisoners who escaped in transit between May 2010 and March 2013</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Category</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 10</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 11</p></td><td><p>Cat B</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 11</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 11</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August 11</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 11</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 12</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 12</p></td><td><p>Potential Category A</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October 12</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November12</p></td><td><p>Uncategorised</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of both escapes and absconds have reduced significantly in recent years. Figures for the number of escapes and absconds since 1995 are provided in the Prison Digest contained in the Prison and Probation Trusts Performance Statistics. This can be found at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225234/prison-performance-digest-12-13.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225234/prison-performance-digest-12-13.xls</a></p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","190263 ; 190287 ; 190288","2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41035/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41035/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41035/answer",,,,,"54",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many of each category of prisoner released from prison in error since May 2010 are still at large.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","190140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41038","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-02","<p>Using centrally held financial records it is not possible to disaggregate the costs of detached duty from other expenses claimed by staff without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>In order to increase efficiency of deployment, a nationally co-ordinated detached duty scheme has been operating since October 2013. The tables below contain details of all establishments that have received officers on detached duty and the average weekly provision of staff deployed on detached duty each month.</p><p> </p><p>The deployment of prison officers between prisons on detached duty is a regular and normal part of prison resourcing. Deployment outside of the nationally co-ordinated scheme which began in October is not recorded centrally. For this reason, information on the number of establishments and staff using detached duty prior to 21 October 2013 is not available.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","190148 ; 190153","2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41038/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41038/answer","190148, 190151,190153.doc","190148, 190151,190153.doc","Table 1","Table 1","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41038/answer",,,,,"54",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which prisons have reported staff shortages that required staff to be called in from another prison in each month since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","190151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41039","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-02","<p>Using centrally held financial records it is not possible to disaggregate the costs of detached duty from other expenses claimed by staff without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>In order to increase efficiency of deployment, a nationally co-ordinated detached duty scheme has been operating since October 2013. The tables below contain details of all establishments that have received officers on detached duty and the average weekly provision of staff deployed on detached duty each month.</p><p> </p><p>The deployment of prison officers between prisons on detached duty is a regular and normal part of prison resourcing. Deployment outside of the nationally co-ordinated scheme which began in October is not recorded centrally. For this reason, information on the number of establishments and staff using detached duty prior to 21 October 2013 is not available.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","190148 ; 190151","2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41039/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41039/answer","190148, 190151,190153.doc","190148, 190151,190153.doc","Table 1","Table 1","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41039/answer",,,,,"54",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many staff in the Prison Service have been on detached duty in each month since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","190153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41047","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-02","<p>Using centrally held financial records it is not possible to disaggregate the costs of detached duty from other expenses claimed by staff without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>In order to increase efficiency of deployment, a nationally co-ordinated detached duty scheme has been operating since October 2013. The tables below contain details of all establishments that have received officers on detached duty and the average weekly provision of staff deployed on detached duty each month.</p><p> </p><p>The deployment of prison officers between prisons on detached duty is a regular and normal part of prison resourcing. Deployment outside of the nationally co-ordinated scheme which began in October is not recorded centrally. For this reason, information on the number of establishments and staff using detached duty prior to 21 October 2013 is not available.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","190151 ; 190153","2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41047/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41047/answer","190148, 190151,190153.doc","190148, 190151,190153.doc","Table 1","Table 1","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41047/answer",,,,,"54",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much was spent on (a) travel, (b) accommodation and (c) subsistence costs for detached duty cover for staff in the Prison Service in each month since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","190148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41078","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-06","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-03-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41078/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41078/answer","PQ 190220.pdf","PQ 190220.pdf","Unemployment - ONS Letter","Unemployment - ONS Letter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41078/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the average duration of unemployment or inactivity is of those who become unemployed or inactive having previously been in employment for (a) less than six months, (b) between six months and a year, (c) between one and two years, (d) between two and three years, (e) between three and four years, (f) between four and five years, (g) between five and 10 years and (h) 10 or more years.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","190220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41090","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-06","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-03-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41090/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41090/answer","PQ 190382.pdf","PQ 190382.pdf","Eating Disorder - ONS Letter","Eating Disorder - ONS Letter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41090/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people with an eating disorder died in the UK in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","190382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41091","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-10","<p>The Government Digital Service is working with other Government departments and agencies across the country, making 25 of the most significant Government services digital by default. The 25 services being transformed can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/transformation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/transformation</a>. A list of all transactions can be found on the Transactions Explorer at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/performance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/performance</a></p><p>We recognise that not all users are online, so assisted digital support will be available to those users that need it.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-03-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41091/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41091/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what services his Department provides that are (a) available online only and (b) planned to move to online only.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","190359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41154","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-06","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-03-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41154/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41154/answer","PQ 902867.pdf","PQ 902867.pdf","Underemployment - ONS Letter","Underemployment - ONS Letter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/41154/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-03-03",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent assessment he has made of the level of underemployment.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","902867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40779","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-06","<p>Central government&rsquo;s direct SME spend increased from &pound;3 billion in 2009-10 (6.5%) to &pound;4.5 billion (10.5%) in 2012-13. In addition, figures provided by major government suppliers indicate that SMEs have benefited from a further &pound;4 billion (9.4%) in indirect spend through the supply chain for 2012 to 2013.</p><p>Building on central government reforms to make its business more accessible to small and medium sized businesses, the Government published in <em>Small Business Great Ambition</em>, the next steps in taking forward Lord Young&rsquo;s recommendations to create an SME-friendly &lsquo;single market&rsquo; for public procurement.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-03-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40779/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40779/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40779/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-02-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress his Department has made in enabling small and medium-sized enterprises to tender for Government procurement contracts.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","190087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40780","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the Hon. Member for Livingston on 16 December 2013 (Official Report) Column Ref: 453W. </p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-03-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40780/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40780/answer","Graeme Morrice - Referral Answer.docx","Graeme Morrice - Referral Answer.docx","Referral Answer for Member","Referral Answer for Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40780/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-02-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many firms in (a) Cannock Chase constituency and (b) Staffordshire have been awarded Government procurement contracts in the last four years.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","190085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40792","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-03-05","<p> </p><p>The electoral register has been the basis for parliamentary boundary reviews since the creation of the independent Boundary Commissions. The Government does not believe that using population figures derived from Census data would provide a better basis for a boundary review than using the electoral register. Importantly, the electoral register is updated annually, and census figures will include persons who are not eligible to register to vote, for example on grounds of citizenship or age.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-03-05T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40792/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40792/answer",,,,,"58",,,"2014-02-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what assessment he has made of the (a) fairness, (b) accuracy and (c) completeness of using the (i) census and midterm census and (ii) electoral register to determine the size of constituencies when drawing boundaries.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","190096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40793","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-03-10","<p> </p><p>The Government has made no such assessment.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-03-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40793/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40793/answer",,,,,"58",,,"2014-02-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what assessment he has made of the potential benefits of bringing forward legislative proposals to make voting compulsory as a means of increasing voter turnout and engagement.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","190095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40536","Leader of the House of Lords","false","2014-03-13","<p>Of the 13 questions to the Ministry of Justice that remained unanswered after 10 working days on 27 February, all but one have now been answered. <br><br>I take the matter of late answers to Questions for Written Answer very seriously. My office reviews the &lsquo;Questions unanswered after 10 working days&rsquo; in <em>House of Lords Business </em>every day. As soon as a question appears in this section of <em>House of Lords Business</em>, my office contacts the relevant department&rsquo;s Parliamentary Team, and they remain in contact with the Parliamentary Team and the Minister&rsquo;s Private Office until the question is answered. <br><br>I have also recently taken the opportunity to discuss the need for timely answers with members of the front bench in this House.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Hill of Oareford",,"2014-03-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40536/answer","Biography information for Lord Hill of Oareford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/40536/answer",,,,,"92",,,"2014-02-27",,"2","House of Lords","To ask the Leader of the House what discussions he has had with Ministers in the Ministry of Justice with regard to the 13 questions asked of that department out of the 27 which remained unanswered after 10 working days on 27 February.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL5681"
