"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39680","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-03","<p>Promotion in the Cabinet Office is based on merit and suitability for the post in question.</p><p>The requested statistics on promotion are not readily available. However, we estimate that male staff constituted 51% of all those promoted since April 2011. This closely reflects the overall proportion currently working in my Department.</p><p>Figures for ethnicity and disability are not available. Cabinet Office does not compel staff to declare against workforce diversity indicators, including ethnicity and disability.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","189156 ; 189176","2014-03-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39680/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39680/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-02-24",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of civil servants in his Department who were promoted in each of the last five years were (a) male and (b) female.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","189136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39698","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-03-03","<p>Building on the successes of City Deals, all 39 Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEPs) have been invited to develop Strategic Economic Plans to set out what needs to be done to boost growth in their area. </p><p>As part of each Strategic Economic Plan, a Growth Deal bid is being developed for negotiation with central government for the allocation of the Local Growth Fund.</p><p>The Local Growth Fund will be at least &pound;2 billion a year from 2015/16. As a result of this, all parts of England are able to access and benefit from this initiative.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-03-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39698/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39698/answer",,,,,"58",,,"2014-02-24",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what progress he has made on identifying areas not included in the first or second wave of the City Deals programme as eligible for subsequent initiatives.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","189252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39732","Home Office","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>We are unable to provide figures specific to asylum cases awaiting travel <br>documents. This information is only held within paper case files, which would <br>mean this question could only be answered through a disproportionately <br>expensive manual case search.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39732/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39732/answer",,,,,"1",,,"2014-02-24",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum cases were awaiting decision for travel documents on 1 February 2014.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","189239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39768","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-10","<p> </p><p>Relocation of Government staff outside of London and the South East continues to be considered, amongst other options, to deliver the savings set out at the Spending Review and increase the efficiency of the Government&rsquo;s estate. Reducing and rationalising the estate could result in relocations, although there is no centrally driven relocation target to this effect. Workforce planning is primarily the responsibility of each individual Department to determine.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire","HL5483 ; HL5484","2014-03-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39768/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39768/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-02-24",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their policy on the relocation of civil servants from London and the South-East of England to other regions of the country.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL5482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39769","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-10","<p> </p><p>Relocation of Government staff outside of London and the South East continues to be considered, amongst other options, to deliver the savings set out at the Spending Review and increase the efficiency of the Government&rsquo;s estate. Reducing and rationalising the estate could result in relocations, although there is no centrally driven relocation target to this effect. Workforce planning is primarily the responsibility of each individual Department to determine.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire","HL5482 ; HL5484","2014-03-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39769/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/39769/answer",,,,,"53",,,"2014-02-24",,"2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many civil servants have been transferred from London and the South-East of England to other regions of the country since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL5483"
